               <head>Ta'rikh-i Mahabatjang, tract</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tārīkh-i Mahābat Jang by Yūsuf ʿAlī Khān ibn Ghulām ʿAlī Khān</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n83129170 http://lccn.loc.gov/n84029362 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh97003385 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4025-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656321.0x000001 viaf_116714286">Yūsuf ʿAlī Khān ibn Ghulām ʿAlī Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656321.0x000001 viaf_116714286" type="supplied">يوسف على خان ابن غلام على خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8089">Tārīkh-i Mahābat Jang</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8089">تٲريخ مهابت جنگ</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Alternative title on title page: Aḥvāl-i salāṭīn-i Hind</p>
                        <p>History of the Navvāb-Nāẓim of the Mughal province of Bengal, Bihar, and Orissa, ʿAlī Virdī Khān Mahābat Jang (d. 1169 / 1756) and his successor, Navvāb-Nāẓim Shujāʿ al-Dawlah (d. 1170 / 1757), completed at Ilāhābād (Allahabad), in 1177 / 1763</p>
                        <p>The author also wrote the Ḥadīqat al-ṣafāʾ (I.O.Islamic 3972)</p>
                        <p>Tract 1 of 6</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                     <filiation>Copied from a manuscript in the library of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, Ms. D.19 (Ivanow 205)</filiation>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
